recipes.ingredients:
2 garlic cloves, crushed
6 tbsp olive oil
2 x 400g cans chopped tomatoes
2 tbsp tomato purée
4 aubergines, cut into long, 5mm thick slices
85g parmesan (or vegetarian alternative), freshly grated
20g pack basil, leaves torn
1 egg, beaten
Lasagna
Ricotta
recipes.directions:
1. Heat oven to 200C/fan 180C/gas 6. In a shallow pan, mix together the garlic and 4 tbsp of the olive oil. Cook over a high heat for 3 mins, tip in the tomatoes, then simmer for 8 mins, stirring every now and then. Stir in the tomato purée.

2. Meanwhile, heat a griddle pan until very hot. Brush a few of the aubergines with a little oil, then add to the pan. Cook over a high heat until well browned and cooked through, about 5-7 mins. Turn them halfway through cooking. Lift onto kitchen paper and do the next batch.

3. When all the aubergines are cooked, lay a few of them in the bottom of an ovenproof dish, then spoon over some sauce. Sprinkle with Parmesan and basil leaves. Add seasoning, then repeat this process with the remaining ingredients. Finally, pour the egg over the top, sprinkle over a little more Parmesan, then bake for 20 mins or until the topping is golden.
recipes.name: Aubergine, tomato & Parmesan bake (Melanzane alla Parmigiana) 2

recipes.ingredients:
250 gram pastinaak
200 gram wortel
4 kruimige aardappels
2 braadworsten
melk
25 gram boter
zout en peper
recipes.directions:
Schil de pastinaak, de wortel en de aardappels. Snijd ze in stukjes die ongeveer even snel gaar koken. Kook het nu in ongeveer 30 minuten gaar. Bak ondertussen een de worsten zachtjes in een koekenpan. Warm in een steelpan een beetje melk op.

Stamp de pastinaak, aardappel en wortel tot een mooie puree. Roer zoveel melk erdoor totdat je een lekkere puree hebt. Roer ook de boter de door om het nog smeuïger te maken. Breng op smaak met peper en zout. Schep de stamppot op het bord. Leg op elk bord een braadworst. Klop het aanbaksel met een scheutje water los in de pan. Giet de jus over de stamppot. Eet smakelijk!
recipes.name: Pastinaak wortelstamppot met worst

recipes.ingredients:
1 tbsp vegetable oil
1 large onion, chopped
1 garlic clove, chopped
1-2 tbsp madras curry paste (we used Patak's)
400g can tomatoes
200ml vegetable stock
sustainable white fish fillets, skinned and cut into big chunks
rice or naan bread
recipes.directions:
1. Heat the oil in a deep pan and gently fry the onion and garlic for about 5 mins until soft. Add the curry paste and stir-fry for 1-2 mins, then tip in the tomatoes and stock.

2. Bring to a simmer, then add the fish. Gently cook for 4-5 mins until the fish flakes easily. Serve immediately with rice or naan
recipes.name: Super-quick fish curry
